  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Imprisonment\n- Corporate sanctions\n\n5. Reporting Obligations\n- Financial institutions must report suspicious transactions\n- Large cash transaction reporting\n- Cross-border money transfer documentation\n\n6. Enforcement Agencies\n- FinCEN (Financial Crimes Enforcement Network)\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n7. Prevention Strategies\n- Risk-based approach\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Ongoing monitoring\n- Internal compliance programs\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes and terrorist financing.",
